RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 3 1M Turf CR: 72. Claiming Purse 22500. FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of Three Races At A Mile Or Over Allowed 2 lbs. Two Such Races Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000 (Races Where Entered For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered) (Condition Eligibility). (If deemed ina dvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUPER CARO raced in the three path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the far bend, drifted out and bumped with FREE SHOT in upper stretch and held a narrow margin to the wire from there. ELSA'S ROCKET raced in the two path around the first turn, trailed the field on the outside up the backstretch, swung out to the six path to began a bid approaching the quarter pole and gained ground late. X Y LADY saved ground around the first bend, dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path around the far turn and kept on in the lane. FREE SHOT raced in the three path around the first turn, dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the four path around the second turn, was bumped and forced to steady when SUPER CARO came into his lane in upper stretch and finished evenly in the final furlong. INFLUENTIALOUS chased the leader on the inside through the opening half mile, saved ground around the far turn and faded in the stretch. GENERAL ROBINSON raced in the four path early, tracked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the five path coming around the far bend, ran into traffic and altered his route near the eighth pole and flattened out from there. DR. BELLA saved ground around the first turn, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the inside, navigated the far turn from the two path and was empty in the lane. THE RIDER OF HORSE SIX, FREE SHOT, CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST HORSE FIVE, SUPER CARO, CITING INTERFERENCE IN UPPER STRETCH. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS MADE INTO THE SAME INCIDENT. UPON REVIEW, HORSE FIVE, SUPER CARO, WAS DISQUALIFIED AND PLACED SIXTH FOR INTERFERENCE WITH BOTH HORSE SIX, FREE SHOT, AND HORSE SEVEN, GENERAL ROBINSON NEAR THE EIGHTH POLE.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 7 1 3/8M Turf CR: 93. Starter Handicap Purse 25000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES, FOUR-YEARS-OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $16,000 OR LESS IN 2022-23. PURSE $25,000 (includes $1,000 from FOA). WEIGHTS: Tuesday, March 21, 2023. Starters and riders to be named through the entry box by the usual time of closing. HIGH WEIGHTS PREFERRED. CONDITION ELIGIBILITY. CLOSED SUNDAY, MARCH 19, 2023 WITH 15 NOMINATIONS.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: INANNA'S QUEST trailed the field from the two path through the opening half mile, began to move up the second time around the oval, began a bid from the four path coming around the far turn, kicked clear in the stretch and held that margin to the wire. PANOTTI raced in the middle of the pack in the two path through the first mile, swung out to the five path coming around the third turn, launched a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground late. FALL MOON raced in the two path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack for the run up the backstretch, navigated the far bend from the four path and kept on in the stretch. PACIFIC PRINCESS saved ground early, chased the leader far behind that rival around the second turn and up the backstretch, continued around the third turn in the two path and was outkicked in the lane. COOL FRONT raced off the pace in the two path through the opening mile and never threatened. SLIME QUEEN raced in the two path in the middle of the pack around the first turn and the first time by the stands, saved ground around the final turn and was empty in the stretch. KATIES A LADY opened up a commanding lead while saving ground the first time around the oval, was caught while racing on the rail entering the stretch and tired quickly from there. BEAUTIFUL TIZ raced off the pace while saving ground through the early going, dropped back to trail the field coming up the backstretch and was eased to the wire.

TITHED bumped with the horse to his inside at the start, settled in the middle of the pack for the run up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the two path and tired in the stretch.
